.TH LESS(1),User Commands,LESS(1)

.SH NAME
less - view a file one screen at a time

.SH SYNOPSIS
less [-h] [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
less displays file a screenful at a time, pausing after each page for a keystroke.
If no file is given, less reads from standard input.

If standard input is not a keyboard (for example, when less is at the end of a pipeline), less prints the entire input without pausing.

Tabs are expanded to 8 columns.

The cx16os less is essentially the same program as more(1);
both share the same implementation and accept the same keys.

.SH KEYS
space, f, PgDn: advance one full page

d: advance a half page

Enter, cursor-down: advance one line

q: quit

.SH OPTIONS
-h: Print a short usage summary and exit 0.

.SH EXIT STATUS
0: File displayed to completion, or quit requested.

1: The specified file could not be opened, or an unknown option was given.

.SH SEE ALSO
more(1)
